<p>An essay by Yufal Noah Harari, the author of Sapien and Homo Deus in his familiar style of writing. He shares his view about the current pandemic and laid out different scenarios that could happen.</p>

<p>A test to citizenship, a choice between privacy and health, between nationality and global collaboration.</p>

<p>n.b: As usual sometimes it seems that he oversimplified things and make it look like there are only two choices.</p>

